<span class='caption'>Bogged down</span>
</div>WHEN Juan Manuel Santos became president of Colombia in August 2010 he promised that investment in upgrading transport infrastructure would become one of the “motors” of his country’s economy. It was a well-judged priority. Difficult geography—the Andes split into three chains and the Pacific coast is backed by jungle—as well as poor roads mean that Colombia has the second-fewest vehicles per person in South America. Cutting transport costs is crucial to boosting the competitiveness of the country’s hard-pressed manufacturers, who have suffered from the strength of the currency, and to overcoming the isolation that is at the root of the country’s socioeconomic inequalities.But after three years in office, the government’s critics complain that its fine talk on infrastructure has yet to be matched by much action. Official hopes are pinned on an ambitious programme of public-private partnerships (PPPs), set out in glossy PowerPoint slides and aimed at attracting $20 billion of mainly private investment into road schemes over six years. A new National Infrastructure Agency (ANI) has drawn up a standardised contract for such...</p>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:120:"http://www.economist.com/news/americas/21580497-ambitious-plan-struggles-get-drawing-board-taking-slow-road?fsrc=rss|ame";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:107:"http://www.economist.com/news/americas/21580497-ambitious-plan-struggles-get-drawing-board-taking-slow-road";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:11:"isPermaLink";s:5:"false";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:30:"Thu, 04 July 2013 15:04:17 GMT";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:5;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:40:"
      
      
      
      
      
